Detailed Description

Every message has an unique id and and may get the following kind of message category:
  • MC_SYSTEM: For default messages. After passing a message to the message-router, the messages are broadcasted to all applications. Note that an application must register itself for messages it wants to receive.
  • MC_FOCUS: For messages, which should be send to the focused application/control. The applications don not need to register for messages which have the category MC_FOCUS.
  • MC_CONTEXT: For messages which should be forwarded to one specific context only. Note that each message with the category MC_CONTEXT is an instance of the class ContextMsg and hence contains a pointer to the ExecutionContext, which should get the message. The context does not need to register for messages with the category MC_CONTEXT. Messages of the category MC_CONTEXT only make sense for asynchronous messages, which are sent using method Message::Post().
  • MC_APP: Only for backward compatibility. Application is derived from ExecutionContext.
  • MC_CONTROL: For messages which should be forwarded to one specific control only. Note that each message with the category MC_CONTROL is an instance of the class ControlMsg and hence contains a pointer to the control, which should get the message. Messages of the category MC_CONTROL only make sense for synchronous messages, which are send by application.SendSelf(...).
  • MC_IPC: For messages (inter process communication) to communication between applications, containers and signal-handler. After passing a message to the message-router, the messages are broadcast to all applications. Note that an application must register itself for messages it wants to receive. (same functionality as MC_SYSTEM)
  • MC_BROADCAST: For messages which should be broadcast to every application. No registration for these message is needed!
  • MC_SIGNAL: For internal messages, which are to protocol stack via SignalHandler (only to be used in ADC & ASC)
  • MC_AT: For internal messages, which are used to an possibly existing AtHandler (APC stack communication modul like the SignalHandler) Other message categories are available (see class MsgCategory for details), but are used only internally.
